block basic
  form.form
    .form_group
      label First Name
      input(type="text" placeholder="John")

    .form_group
      label Last Name
      input(type="text" placeholder="Smith")

    .form_group
      legend Issue size
      label
        input(type="radio" name="issue")
        |  Small issue
      label
        input(type="radio" name="issue")
        |  Regular issue
      label
        input(type="radio" name="issue")
        |  Large issue

    .form_group
      label Shipping options
      label
        input(type="checkbox")
        |  Fast shipping
      label
        input(type="checkbox")
        |  Gift-wrapping

    .form_group
      label Subscription frequency
      select
        option Daily
        option Weekly
        option Monthly
        option Yearly

    .form_group
      label Bio
      textarea

    input(value="Subscribe" type="submit" role="button")

  .if-semantic
    :markdown
      Wrap sets of form elements in an element using `form_group()` to keep
      proper spacing.

          <form>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="fname">First name</label>
              <input name="fname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="lname">Last name</label>
              <input name="lname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="group">
              <label>Issue Size</label> 
              <label for="small">
                <input name="small" type="checkbox" />
                Small
              </label>
              <label for="regular">
                <input name="regular" type="checkbox" />
                Regular
              </label>
              <label for="large">
                <input name="large" type="checkbox" />
                Large
              </label>
            </div>
            ...
            <input type="submit" />
          </form>

          form {
            @include form();
          }
          .group {
            @include form_group();
          }

block variations
  :markdown
    ### Horizontal

    `textarea` elements are not included in default styling of horizontal
    forms.

  form.form-horizontal
    .form_group.form_group-horizontal
      label First Name
      input(type="text" placeholder="John")

    .form_group.form_group-horizontal
      label Last Name
      input(type="text" placeholder="Smith")

    .form_group.form_group-horizontal
      label Industry
      select
        option Academic
        option Automotive
        option Finance
        option Government
        option Medical
        option Restaurant
        option Technology

    input(type="submit" role="button")

  .if-semantic
    :markdown
      Both the `form()` and `form_group()` mixins need to pass in `horizontal`
      as a parameter. This is because it is possible to have a vertical
      form with both horizontal and vertical form groups

          <form>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="fname">First name</label>
              <input name="fname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="lname">Last name</label>
              <input name="lname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="industry">Industry</label>
              <select name="industry">
                ...
              </select>
            </div>
            <input type="submit" />
          </form>

          form {
            @include form('horizontal');
          }
          .group {
            @include form_group('horizontal');
          }

  .ifnot-semantic
    :markdown
      Both the `.form` and `.form_group` classes need to use `.form-horizontal`
      and `.form_group-horizontal` classes respectively. This is because it is possible to have a vertical
      form with both horizontal and vertical form groups

          <form>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="fname">First name</label>
              <input name="fname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="lname">Last name</label>
              <input name="lname" type="text" />
            </div>
            <div class="group">
              <label for="industry">Industry</label>
              <select name="industry">
                ...
              </select>
            </div>
            <input type="submit" />
          </form>

          form {
            @include form('horizontal');
          }
          .group {
            @include form_group('horizontal');
          }

